Vercel Web Analytics Installation Complete
===========================================

Successfully installed and configured Vercel Web Analytics for this Next.js App Router project.

## Changes Made:

### 1. Package Installation
- Installed `@vercel/analytics` package version ^1.4.1
- Updated package.json with the new dependency
- Updated package-lock.json with the resolved dependency tree

### 2. Layout Configuration (app/layout.tsx)
- Added import for Analytics component: `import { Analytics } from "@vercel/analytics/next"`
- Added `<Analytics />` component at the end of the body section
- Component placement follows Vercel's official documentation for Next.js App Router

### 3. Files Modified
- `app/layout.tsx` - Added Analytics import and component
- `package.json` - Added @vercel/analytics dependency
- `package-lock.json` - Updated with new dependency resolution

## Implementation Details:

The implementation follows the official Vercel Analytics quickstart guide for Next.js App Router projects:
- Used the framework-specific import from `@vercel/analytics/next`
- Placed the Analytics component at the bottom of the body tag
- Preserved all existing functionality and code structure
- No breaking changes introduced

## Verification Results:

✅ Build: Successfully completed (npm run build)
✅ TypeScript: Compiled without errors
✅ Static Generation: All 22 pages generated successfully
✅ Linter: No new errors introduced (existing project errors unrelated to this change)

## Next Steps:

To fully activate Vercel Web Analytics:
1. Deploy this application to Vercel
2. Navigate to your project's Analytics section in the Vercel dashboard
3. Click the "Enable" button to activate analytics collection
4. After deployment, verify implementation by checking browser Network tab for requests to `/_vercel/insights/*`

## Notes:

- The Analytics component will automatically track page views and web vitals
- No additional configuration is required in the code
- Analytics data will only be collected after enabling in the Vercel dashboard
- The component is tree-shakeable and will not impact bundle size in development
